description: ¡La salsa no tiene fronteras! / Salsa knows no borders! Este 17 de mayo, prepárate para una de las mejores rumbas de salsa en BC.
location: 1149 Granville ST, VANCOUVER, BC, V6Z1M1, CA

description: Get ready to grow your own delicious salsa ingredients with this fun, hands-on workshop! In this class, you'll create a vibrant salsa planter, filled with all the fresh ingredients needed for homemade salsa throughout the season.
location: 6375 West Saanich RD, SAANICHTON, BC, V8M1W8, CA

description: Ages 18+. Get ready to set the Hollywood Theatre on fire with irresistible grooves! This Friday night, Empanadas Ilegales invites you to the electric launch of Sancocho Trifásico — along side some amazing acts and surprises, we bring a psychedelic cumbia and salsa extravaganza that will ignite every corner of the dance floor. From the first pulsing beat to the final shimmering chord, we’re conjuring a sonic storm of tropical heat, surf‑tinged reverbs, and spicy rhythms that refuse to let you stand still. Grab your crew, lace up your dancing shoes, and surrender to the magic of the night. When cumbia collides with psychedelia and salsa gets drenched in surf rock, there’s only one command: MOVE WITHOUT LIMITS!
location: 3123 Broadway W, VANCOUVER, BC, V6K2H2, CA

event_name: Learn to Dance Salsa and Bachata - First Class Free (Sunday)
description: Ready to get your hips moving, feet stomping, and heart pumping to the rollicking rhythms of la música latina? Whether you're a complete newbie or just looking to sharpen your skills, our fun and friendly classes will have you grooving in no time. Bonus : Your first class is absolutely free! Feel the energy, embrace the music, and unleash the dancer within! No partner? No problem—you’ll meet new friends while learning new moves. Two left feet? Don’t worry! We’ll have you grooving with confidence before you know it, and wondering why you didn’t start sooner.
location: 345 West Broadway, Vancouver, BC V5Y 1P8
price: Free for first class, $30 for 3 classes, $50 for 6 classes, $15 drop-ins

description: Get ready to swing into action with our Swing Series! Led by expert instructor Kat Single-Dain, and often featuring awesome lead Laz Savic, our classes cover a variety of styles including charleston, lindy hop, and vernacular jazz. This series is for Beginners AND those who have taken our series or other beginner series before!! --We will be giving individual attention to folks in order to challenge everyone -- great for those who have taken either none, one or two of Kat's series before. This series of 6 weekly classes begins on September and takes place every Friday for a total of six classes from 6-7pm. We will usually play music from 7-730pm at the space after your lesson so that you can stay and practice!
location: The Dusty Flowerpot Cabaret, 2050 Scotia Street, Vancouver, BC V5T 4T1

event_name: The Hoss Mountain Stringband PLUS Ella Korth
description: A fabulous double bill! Featuring the Old Time and Bluegrass badass band, Hoss Mountain Stringband, plus the lovely & talented Ella Korth!
location: Upstairs Lounge, Oak Bay Recreation Centre, 1975 Bee Street, Oak Bay, BC V8R 5E6

event_name: Hotham Sound Recordings: Resonance Beneath the Maple Tree
description: A special performance in nature on Salt Spring Island, celebrating the Pacific Northwest label Hotham Sound's 10-year anniversary. Features artists KR75, Midi Janitor, Playback Head, Dove Magic, and Sean Evans.
location: 279 Rainbow RD, SALT SPRING ISLAND, BC, V8K2M3, CA
price: $20 in advance and $25 at the door (cash only). Kids under 16 attend for free.

event_name: Swing into Spring with Sunny Shams
description: A fun-filled event full of music, dancing, and good vibes to kick off the spring season with live music and exciting activities for all ages.
location: 1720 McTavish RD, NORTH SAANICH, BC, V8L5T9, CA

description: Come hang out, swap some clothes, and maybe even learn a dance step or two! Organized by Team Tandem and Patchwork Repair Hub, a Clothes & Seeds Swap Event that brings the Vancouver community together for a meaningful exchange of clothes, seeds, stories, and embraces. Includes a special section just for tango clothes and an Intro to Tango Dancing.
location: 2765 29th AVE E, VANCOUVER, BC, V5R1V5, CA

event_name: 7th Annual WTF Beerlympics In Support of Canadian Mental Health Association
description: Charity beer consumption! All profits go support Canadian Mental Health Association. 10 teams will compete in modified drinking games to win a big shiny KEG. All teams will play all games. This event has sold out before and is limited to 10 TEAMS ONLY. Doors @ 6:00pm (Games start at 7:00pm). No Refunds.
location: 1 Sixth AVE E, NEW WESTMINSTER, BC, V3L4G6, CA

description: This is the cheapest, stupidest and silliest show East Van has to offer! Amy Grindhouse is bringing her unique brand of off the wall humour to the Birdhouse stage, encouraging all performers to take a big swing and try something new or something ridiculous without fear of judgment. Featuring: Velvet Ryder, PM, Bliss, Acacia, Genesis, Skim. ALL NIGHT HAPPY HOUR. Doors at 7pm, Show at 8pm SHARP. CHEAP & CHEERFUL DANCE PARTY at 10pm! All guests are welcome to stay and dance at Cheap & Cheerful after the show FOR FREE!
location: 44 4th AVE W, VANCOUVER, BC, V5Y1G3, CA

description: Join us for the FIRST UNITED 140th Anniversary Golf Tournament on May 26! Swing into action and support FIRST's essential work in the DTES! The tournament is presented by Terra Breads in support of our work providing essential services, community connection, and healing in Vancouver’s Downtown Eastside! This year, we need to raise $210,000 in order to meet the complex needs of those we serve in the Downtown Eastside. We hope you’ll join us for this fun tradition of community-connection and giving back. Space is limited and this signature event regularly sells out. Your ticket includes a golf cart, 18 hole shotgun competition, a revitalizing lunch, as well as a premium steak and salmon banquet dinner.
location: University Golf Club, 5185 University Blvd. Vancouver, BC V6T 1X5

event_name: Songs of the Sea featuring Fergus O'Byrne and Jim Payne
description: Come join us for an evening of traditional sea shanties and folk songs with the talented Fergus O'Byrne and Jim Payne! Get ready to be transported to the rugged shores of Newfoundland as these talented musicians serenade you with tales of the sea. With Nanaimo's own Fiddelium as their guests, don't miss this unique opportunity to experience the rich cultural heritage of Newfoundland through music.

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Bachata Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

description: Class Description This class is for experienced dancers and performers that want to continue to push themselves with more complex techniques. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Monday from 8:00- 9:00pm Must have instructor permission to attend. No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Salsa Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.

description:
Rehearsal for our Ladies Team. Open to team members by audition only. Team Description
Auditioned performance groups with rehearsals twice a week plus additional class and social requirements. event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha- Beginner Intermediate
dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is dancers that have completed the Fundamentals course and want to continue to improve their social dancing using the techniques they have learned. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

Auditioned performance groups with rehearsals twice a week plus additional class and social requirements. The group has performed locally as well as in Puerto Rico, New York, Atlanta, Seattle and Chicago. By audition only. Open to team members by audition only. Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Salsa Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: We are excited to bring you dancing the 4th Friday of every month at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 7:45pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:00pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. All ages welcome. $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: Victoria Edelweiss Club, 108 Niagara St, Victoria, BC V8V 1E9, Canada

description: Celebrate the vibrant spirit of Carnaval with us on Sunday, April 27th, 2025, for an evening of Latin social dancing! As we embrace the festive atmosphere of Carnaval, come dressed in your most colorful attire and you’ll be entered into a raffle for a chance to win a special prize. Event Schedule: Doors Open: 4:15 PM Beginner Dance Lesson: 4:30 PM - 5:00 PM The dance style varies each month. Social Dancing: 5:00 PM - 8:30 PM Join us in James Bay at 111 Superior Street, where we’ll be heating things up with Salsa, Bachata, Kizomba, and Merengue. Although song requests aren’t taken during the event, you’re welcome to share your favorite tunes in our WhatsApp community group beforehand, and we’ll consider them for our playlist. Admission: $15 for General Admission $12 for Students with a valid ID We accept debit, credit, or cash (cash preferred). Please note that a small fee applies for debit or credit transactions. This event is open to everyone—no partner or previous dance experience is required. All ages, bodies, and abilities are warmly welcomed! Whether you’re dancing the night away or simply enjoying the Carnaval spirit, everyone is invited to be part of this vibrant community event. Don’t forget to bring a water bottle to stay hydrated throughout the evening. Monthly Events: This event is part of our ongoing series held on the last Sunday of every month from September to May. Make sure to mark your calendars! As a community collective non-profit association, we truly value your continuous support. All funds are reinvested to improve the quality of our gatherings and to create even more memorable experiences for you. It costs approximately $4,000 to run basic events for the year, covering costs like insurance, permits, equipment, venue rentals, administration, and website maintenance. Disclaimer: Please be aware that videos and photos may be taken during our events and could be posted on social media or online later. We appreciate your understanding!
location: 111 Superior St, Victoria, BC V8V 1T2, Canada
price: $15 for General Admission, $12 for Students with a valid ID

description: NEW CONCEPT - NEW VIBE - INCLUSIVE ENVIRONMENT For this edition, we're have integrated Bachata in all of our indoor and outdoor activities. What to expect?? Locally and Internationally renowned instructors, teaching: Sensual Bachata, Urban & Fusion Bachata, Semba, Kizomba, Urban Kiz, Tarraxinha, Tarraxo, Douceur, Afro Beat, Afro House, Kuduro and More! ALL IN ONE: - Over 27.000 square feet of space - 4 ROOMS: BACHATA - KIZOMBA - URBAN KIZ - AFRO BEATS and REGGAETON - After party room go until 6-7am with (Douceur, Tarraxinha and Sweet Kiz) VIKF 6th Edition is offering you: *4 days of workshops *3 day-time socials *4 nights of dancing, *3 afterparties until 6-7am *30Hours + of workshops *40H + of dancing * 2 educational sessions of Cultural Aspect of African dances * 1 Gala Night of celebration of Multiculturalism, Diversity, the Arts including performances and fashion shows by African Designers

description: Pachanga Latina presents The Mexican Independence Party with Paula Zerpa & Andrea Zuñiga singing Cumbias, Rancheras, Salsa & Merengue music, also featuring Fiesta Latina Folklore Dancers. Music by Dj Moses El Pachanguero playing the best Salsa, Reggaeton, Cumbia, Bachata, Rock en Español and more. Traditional Mexican food available all night by La Tortilla on the run. There will be only 100 tickets to sell in advance. Folks under 18 can use the code UNDER18 for $10 off. 15+ fail to bring your ID will result in not being able to get in and no refund will be made. Children under 15 years of age will have to vacate the premises at 11pm.

description: Foundation Class (6:30–7:35 PM) Perfect for absolute beginners or dancers looking to strengthen their foundation! Intermediate Class (7:35–8:40 PM) Ready to level up? This class is designed for dancers who already feel comfortable with the basics and want to challenge themselves. We’ll dive into more fun patterns while also exploring musicality—how to connect those movements to the music in a more expressive way. Get ready to build confidence, fluidity, and your own unique style! To Register: Send your e-transfer to maximumotion@gmail.com and include in the memo: Foundation, Intermediate, or Both + Lead or Follow

description: Join us for an all-levels balboa dance practice space every Wednesday in Victoria B.C.! We start at 7pm, but you can drop in anytime during the practice space depending on which part you're interested in. Our location at 1741 Duchess Street in a heritage home offers hardwood floors and tea. This is for you if you have something in particular you want to work on, aren't quite sure what you want to be working on or if you want a refresher on the basics.

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

event_name: Texture Your Moves for West Coast Swing
description: We will guide you through practical musicality and movement drills that will 'colour in' any pattern in your repertoire. You'll learn how to do more styling without feeling inhibited or being reckless, preserve your partnership connection while still expressing yourself, enjoy being musical even with partners who are missing skills, and respect the rules of the WCS while learning to bend them. Come learn a super practical & universal way to LEVEL UP your musicality by adding body pulse & groove to add more personality and creativity into basic patterns, then get lots of reps to practice these tactics with the appropriate connection and timing. All the while putting these skills to use immediately in your social dancing! This workshop is for you if you have no idea how to dance differently to different genres of music, so most of your dances look or feel the same. You feel like you are just walking through patterns without any real character to your movement and you feel robotic and stiff. You can do body pulse and contra-body but they are not automatic in your dancing yet. You can't seem to make wise, deliberate choices for texturing your moves to the music. You aren’t able to make your slow tempo songs look distinct from your other genres. Please bring shoes or socks & your own water bottle. Space is limited to 14ppl max. You do NOT need a partner! Call Jay @ (250) 886-4599 if you have any questions.
location: 516 Quadra St, Victoria, BC V8V 3S3, Canada
price: $30 via etransfer (for 2hr workshop) $40 (if paying at the door)

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA
